README for ucon64

REQUIREMENTS

PRE-INSTALL

POST-INSTALL
1. suid root the binary(/usr/bin/ucon64) if you want to use parallel port.

2. run something like this as regular user:
#! /bin/sh
#
if [ ! -e $HOME/.ucon64 ]; then
	mkdir $HOME/.ucon64
fi
if [ ! -e $HOME/.ucon64/dat ]; then
	for dat in `ls -1 /usr/share/ucon64/dat/*.dat`
	do
		ln -s $dat $HOME/.ucon64/`basename $dat`
	done
fi
if [ ! -e $HOME/.ucon64/libdiscmage.so ]; then 
	ln -s /usr/share/ucon64/discmage.so $HOME/.ucon64/discmage.so
fi

RESOURCES
You can download static ucon64 gui binary here:
http://dl.sourceforge.net/ucon64/uf-FOX-1.1-linux-bin.zip
(Making a port for that with all it's deps would be an overkill)